items.title: Oil regulator cracks down on city gas firms; seeks uniform price of piped cooking gas
items.description: The government allocates natural gas priced at lower than market rates, called APM gas, to city gas retailers for sale to households as piped natural gas

items.title: Sona Comstar enters Chinese EV market, forms joint venture with Jinnaite Machinery
items.description: The Gurugram-based firm said it will invest $12 million, while its Chinese counterpart will put $8 million into the joint venture in the first phase

items.title: Passenger vehicles, two-wheelers fuel 22% growth in India's Q1 automobile exports
items.description: Across the segments, the total exports surged to 14,57,461 units in Q1, compared to 11,92,566 units in the same period of previous financial year

items.title: Bajaj Finance MD Anup Kumar Saha resigns, Rajeev Jain to take over
items.description: Significantly, Saha is reportedly seen as the potential candidate for IndusInd Bank's top position of MD and CEO

items.title: Nayara tweaks payment terms for product export tender after EU sanctions
items.description: The company also issued a jet fuel sale tender on Friday, but it remains unclear if it was awarded as the company was looking to change payment terms

items.title: ICICI Bank Q1 FY26: Steady show; will the re-rating continue?
items.description: The bank has shown consistent performance in the past many quarters, amid sectoral concerns like slowing loan growth, muted deposit growth, tight liquidity, asset quality pressure, and tightened regulatory norms

items.title: Tilaknagar shares rally 8 percent on favourable Bom HC ruling, ahead of board's fund raise decision
items.description: The fund raise may be done in one or more tranches through the permitted routes such as a public offer, rights issue, private placement, preferential allotment, Qualified Institutional Placement (QIP), or a combination of these.

items.title: L&T to build India’s maiden green hydrogen plant at IOC's refinery
items.description: The plant will run round-the-clock using renewable energy to supply 10,000 tonnes of green hydrogen annually to IOC for 25 years, a crucial step in India's National Green Hydrogen Mission.

items.title: HDFC Bank Q1 FY26: Will earnings mirror balance sheet strength, going forward?
items.description: The Street continues to keep a close eye on two key variables for HDFC Bank — advances growth and margin, both of which were impacted after the merger

items.title: New CEOs are driving stock surge across India Inc with a 75 percent success rate
items.description: CEO changes have emerged as a strong catalyst for shareholder returns across India Inc. An analysis of BSE 500 companies shows that out of 40 firms with top-level transitions in the last five years, 30 delivered strong post-transition returns—highlighting growing investor faith in new leadership.

items.title: Can CEAT regain margin traction after Q1 FY26?
items.description: Strong volume-led growth offset by margin pressure. The company eyes on H2 as Camso, exports, and premiumisation take hold
